FT  01 OCT 94 / 200 Scottish jobs to be created
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Solectron, the US electronics company, is to invest Pounds 10m in expanding
its printed circuit board assembly plant at Dunfermline, Fife.
The expansion by the California-based company will create 200 jobs by the
end of next year, bringing the total number of workers to 1,000. A new
68,000 sq ft manufacturing unit will be built. Solectron bought the
Dunfermline plant from Philips of the Netherlands in October 1993.
