<BYLINE>
   By DAVID OWEN
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
A Tory-led industry pressure group yesterday urged Mr Kenneth Clarke, the
chancellor, to introduce 100 per cent capital allowances in the Budget next
month as part of a clear strategy for economic growth, David Owen writes.
The Manufacturing and Construction Industries Alliance - chaired by Mr
Nicholas Winterton, Conservative MP for Macclesfield - said the move was
vital to the future prosperity of the UK. The alliance also urged Mr Clarke
to avoid any further tax increases.
Mr Winterton said the government should 'give a boost to the economy'. He
added that this should be 'specifically through lower interest rates, the
introduction of 100 per cent capital allowances in the first year to
encourage industry to invest in the new facilities vital to our continued
competitiveness, and further, carefully targeted investment in the transport
infrastructure and the public-sector building stock'.
