   WASHINGTON
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Mr Bill Clinton, the US president, has no plans to meet Mr Gerry Adams, US
officials repeated yesterday in the face of the Sinn Fein president's
continued campaign for a White House meeting.
'He will meet with officials from the State Department and White House at
the working level, but not here,' said Ms Dee Dee Myers, Mr Clinton's press
