<HEADLINE>
FT  01 OCT 94 / Yeltsin misses Irish talks
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
The steps leading to the Russian presidential aircraft were in place.
Dignitaries including the Irish prime minister Albert Reynolds were gathered
at Shannon airport to greet their guest - but president Boris Yeltsin failed
to appear for official talks.
After a 15-minute delay Mr Reynolds and his entourage returned to the
airport terminal accompanied by Oleg Soskovetz, first Russian deputy prime
minister, who stood in for Mr Yeltsin during the talks.
He said later Mr Yeltsin was 'extremely tired' after a 17-hour flight to
Ireland. On his return to Moscow, Mr Yeltsin told reporters he was feeling
'excellent' and had 'just overslept'.
